CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 2, 1962, pg. 1, reads: "Leaders - Pictured above are Negro leaders who met with candidates Scranton and Van Zandt, last Friday evening in Loendi Club. Standing (left to right) Walter Rainey, John C. Campbell, Mr. Van Zandt, W. P. Young, Louis J. McTurner, Walter Hales, Mr. Scranton, Peter Dillard, Buford Holman, J. R. Williams, Quinn Banks. These men represent Allegheny, Cambria, Lawrence, Beaver, Washington and Westmoreland Counties. Many county chairmen were also represented... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Men, including Walter Rainey, John C. Campbell, James Van Zandt, W. P. Young, Louis J. McTurner, Walter Hales, Pennsylvania gubernatorial candidate William "Bill" Scranton, Peter Dillard, Buford Holman, J. R. Williams, Quinn Banks, gathered for Republican banquet, Loendi Club
